post_text:
In a recent board meeting, the Franklin-McKinley School District urged local, state, and federal governments to identify and complete urgent short-term and long-term infrastructure solutions to address the digital divide for low-income residents.

The Board of Education urged the district administration to continue exploring the district's ability to join the community wireless network project with East Side Union High School District that will bring internet connection to homes throughout the Franklin-McKinley Community.

We will continue to keep you informed on this issue. Together, we will bridge the digital divide!

#FMSDGlobalLearners

post_text:
We are pleased to announce that the Franklin-McKinley School District Board of Education has given direction to the Superintendent to follow district process for considering new curricular content by creating an Ethnic Studies Adoption Committee. Consistent with the Franklin-McKinley School District curriculum adoption process, the stakeholder group will research Ethnic Studies curriculum, review relevant materials, consider the scope of piloting the curriculum with the ultimate goal of presenting a recommendation to the Superintendent and ultimately, the Franklin-McKinley School District Board of Education.

To read the full resolution, visit: www.fmsd.org

On June 23rd, the Franklin-McKinley Board of Trustees passed the following resolution:

"The Franklin-McKinley School District Board of Education stands firmly against bigotry, prejudice, discrimination and inequity in all forms, both institutional and individual. As protests surge in our local community and beyond, the Franklin-McKinley School District Board of Education wishes to affirm its commitment to the wellbeing and safety of Black community members and let them know they are not alone and that our district stands in solidarity with them and their struggle for justice...

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Franklin-McKinley School District declares that Black Lives Matter and joins the movement to fight for freedom, liberation, and justice for the Black community..."

Join the movement for justice and equity. To read the full resolution, visit:
fmsd.org

post_text: Summer is here and Franklin-McKinley School District will be providing home learning packets to keep students engaged this summer! Home learning packets will be available for pick up starting Friday, June 26th during the Grab-N-Go Meal Programs between 11am-1pm. Packets do not need to be returned as they are meant to provide skills practice during the summer break. They will be available on a first come, first served basis. Packets may be downloaded and printed from home as well by clicking on the following link and locations for the Grab-N-Go Meal Programs: https://www.fmsd.org/apps/pages/summer2020. Information about our summer meal program is also now available. We look forward to providing children with healthy meals and engaging learning activities this summer!

post_text:
Hello Franklin-McKinley families -

Your family could be eligible for health services. We are pleased to share this information from our partner, Healthier Kids Foundation. They are offering application assistance for healthcare coverage in Santa Clara County.

----------------------

post_text:
We would like to inform our families of the Pandemic EBT or P-EBT benefits which will provide up to $365 per eligible child for families whose children are eligible for free or reduced-price meals at school.

Families with children who get CalFresh, Medi-Cal or Foster Care benefits do not need to apply. Most will get their P-EBT card in the mail during the month of May. P-EBT cards will begin arriving around May 12, 2020.

Families with children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals and who do not get their P-EBT card in the mail by about May 22, 2020 must apply online before June 30, 2020. The online application will be available beginning today, May 22, 2020 at ca.p-ebt.org. For more information, visit their website: https://www.cdss.ca.gov/home/pandemic-ebt. #FMSDGlobalLearners

*Please note these benefits are provided by the State of California, and not FMSD.

post_text:
At FMSD, we celebrate our diversity and cultures because we believe our differences can bring us together! At Lairon, “Celebrating your Culture” was a very popular Spirit Day!

Layla is Mexican, Filipino and white and born in the USA. On New Year's, she celebrates a tradition with her dad by making and eating corned beef and cabbage for good luck. On Christmas Eve, they make tamales and menudo, another family tradition. And, once a year, they make lumpias.

Who else is proud of their diversity and culture? Share your culture and tradition with us in the comment section! Feel free to add pictures of your dishes, decorations and even traditional clothing! #FMSDGlobalLearners

April was Bilingual Month, but at FMSD, we celebrate throughout the year through our two spectacular Dual Immersion Programs in Spanish and Vietnamese. The Santa Clara County Office of Education hosted a special virtual recognition to recognize the District in two categories:

- Districts with a Signature Practice for Multilingual Learners
- Districts and charter schools that have established a board policy or resolution honoring students with the Pathway and Biliteracy Awards

We are proud to announce that we have established practices for Multilingual Learners and passed Resolution 2020-16 (Pathway to Biliteracy) during the March 24, 2020 Board of Education Meeting. #FMSDGlobalLearners

April is #AutismAwarenessMonth! Our Board of Education passed a Resolution 2020-17 that formally designates April as Autism Awareness Month in our District and encourages the community to show its support for autism awareness.

Autism affects social, communication and behavioral skills. At FMSD, we offer a high-quality learning program for students with autism.

We remain dedicated to using various classroom strategies such as visual icons, structured learning schedules, and supporting adaptive behavior to provide a high-quality learning experience for students with autism. #FMSDGlobalLearners #AutismAwareness

MEAL UPDATE

This is an update from the Franklin-McKinley School District regarding meal pick ups. Starting, Thursday, March 19th Bridges Academy and Sylvandale Middle School will no longer be serving meals. For families who would like to continue picking up meals, schools surrounding Bridges Academy include McKinley, Kennedy, Santee, and Meadows Elementary. For families who would like to continue picking up meals, schools surrounding Sylvandale Middle School include Dahl, Los Arboles, Lairon or Hellyer Elementary. Families may also pick up at any other of the open FMSD schools between 11am and 1pm, Monday-Friday. Thank you for your time and attention.

HOME LEARNING PACKET UPDATE

This is an update from FMSD. Home learning packets will still be available for pick up 3/19-3/20 at all schools between 11am-1pm. As of 3/23, packets will only be available for pick up at the District Service Center.

During this time of school closure, Franklin-McKinley School District will be providing home learning packets and other resources to students and families. Home learning packets will be available for pick up starting tomorrow, March 18th during the meal pick up window of 11am-1pm. Packets do not need to be returned as they are meant to provide skills practice during the school closure period. Packets may be downloaded and printed from home as well by clicking on the link below: https://www.fmsd.org/apps/pages/learningpackets.

We also encourage families to call the following hotline for crisis response services: 1-855-278-4204. For additional resources and support please submit a referral to School Linked Services: http://bit.ly/2wcBaEo.

post_text:
Dear Franklin-McKinley School District Community,

This message is to inform you that due to the newest Public Health recommendations announced earlier today regarding gatherings of 35 to 100 people, our schools will be closed from March 16 through April 3rd. Again, we will be closed from March 16th through April 3rd. This time of closure will allow us as a school district to review the newest guidance from Public Health and how we will proceed after April 3rd. School will remain open today as scheduled and release at the regular time.

Please note that we will be providing breakfast and lunch for pick up to ensure students are still able to receive meals. Further communication on instructions for meal pick up starting on Monday will be forthcoming.

Additionally, we will be communicating in the coming days about how we will continue supporting our students’ education from home. Information about instructional packets and other resources will be made available soon.

Thank you for your patience and understanding. Please monitor our District Facebook page and website for more details.

post_text:
Let's celebrate #WomxnsHistoryMonth

During the month of March, the Franklin-McKinley School District will recognize and honor Womxn's History Month by encouraging our schools and partners to empower young womxn through lesson plans and activities.

We also want to take a moment and recognize Lola Williams, a former Franklin-McKinley Board of Education member. She served on the Board for 12 years until her appointment to the San Jose City Council in 1979. She was known as a champion of minority and womxn's rights. She was also instrumental in the creation of the African American Military History Museum, located in Mississippi. Read more about Lola Williams by visiting www.fmsd.org. #FMSDGlobalLearners

At FMSD, we love celebrations, especially days that inspire and motivate children to read and improve their school performance. That is why we love celebrating #ReadAcrossAmerica!

This past Monday, throughout the District, teachers, community leaders, volunteers and even our Superintendent, Juan Cruz, took the opportunity to read popular, uplifting and memorable books to our students.

Check out the video and celebrate #ReadAcrossAmerica with our #FMSDGlobalLearners!

post_text: Every 10 years, the U.S. Census Bureau undertakes a huge task - counting all the people residing in the United States. This count affects the allocation of funding for our community's public resources (e.g., roads, hospitals, schools), how we plan for the future, and our voice in government. Learn more about the importance of the #2020Census and how to participate: 2020census.gov. #FMSDGlobalLearners

Happy Presidents Day, FMSD community! Originally, we celebrated George Washington and Abraham Lincoln's birthday, but now commemorate every president in our history.

Did you know, President Martin Van Buren was the first president born after the American Revolution. Technically, he was the first American-born president since the previous seven were born in the colonies. What is your favorite president fact? #FMSDGlobalLearners

post_text:
We are proud to announce the launch of our online registration portal!

If you haven’t registered for the 2020-21 school year, you can go online beginning on February 3, 2020. Prior to beginning the online registration process, we recommend that you have the following information prepared.

1. Parent and/or guardian emergency contact information and relatives/designated emergency contacts (i.e., Phone, email, and home address)
2. Child's medical history and health provider
3. Child's general information (i.e., birth date, gender, address, etc.)

Note: Parent/guardian must have an active email address to participate in online enrollment. Upon submission of the online application, you will receive an email from the Franklin-McKinley School District to complete your enrollment which includes supporting documentation that will be submitted to your child's school.

#FMSDGlobalLearners #Enrollment #OnlineRegistration

https://www.fmsd.org/apps/pages/enrollment

A big thank you to Shoes That Fit and Councilmember Maya Esparza for supporting 200 Franklin-McKinley School District students from Dahl, Kennedy, Lairon, and Los Arboles by providing new and comfortable shoes. This was part of its initiative in helping children to learn, grow and thrive. Check out our pictures below! 👟✨

post_text:
A big thank you to College Football Playoff (CFP) Foundation's Extra Yard for Teachers initiative for supporting our efforts, and most of all, our students' futures.

#FMSDGlobalLearners #SeasonofGiving
shared_text:
Extra Yard for Teachers
December 6, 2019 at 5:21 PM ·

Leading up to the Pac-12’s sixth-consecutive football championship game at Levi’s® Stadium today, the Conference and mascots from all 12 universities surprised 12 deserving teachers throughout the San Jose area with awards totaling over $36,000 in connection with the College Football Playoff (CFP) Foundation’s Extra Yard for Teachers initiative. The awards took place as surprises for each teacher and their classrooms over the past two days. All 12 teachers and their classrooms were also welcomed to the championship game his evening to be recognized on the field during the game.

post_text:
In our efforts to expose our students to culture, art and theater, we were happy to host the San Jose City College Theater Department for a modern-day rendition of La Cenicienta in honor of #HispanicHeritageMonth. We thank the San Jose City College Theater Department for lending their skills to make this day special for our #McKinley students!

#McKinley #FMSDGlobalLearners

Como parte de nuestros esfuerzos por exponer a nuestros estudiantes a la cultura, el arte y el teatro, nos complació organizar con el Departamento de Teatro de San Jose City College una representación moderna de La Cenicienta en honor al #MesdelaHerenciaHispana. ¡Agradecemos al Departamento de Teatro de San Jose City College por prestar sus habilidades para hacer que este día fuera especial para nuestros estudiantes de #McKinley!

It's a special time of year! The @SanJosePD volunteered to participate in the Heroes and Helpers Shopping Spree, Shop with a Cop event to help make the holidays a little merrier for our students and community.

We're delighted to have been included in this special annual tradition. A big thank you to everyone who made this possible!

#FMSDGlobalLearners #SeasonofGiving #ShopwithaCop

¡Es una época especial del año! @SanJosePD se ofreció como voluntario para participar en el evento Heroes and Helpers Shopping Spree, Shop with a Cop para ayudar a que las vacaciones sean un poco más felices para nuestros estudiantes y la comunidad.

Estamos encantados de haber sido incluidos en esta tradición anual especial. ¡Muchas gracias a todos los que hicieron esto posible!

#FMSDGlobalLearners #SeasonofGiving #ShopwithaCop

post_text:
We love our #VietnameseDualImmersion program! It gives our students an opportunity to become bilingual and biliterate!

Each program will be enrolling children who will be entering kindergarten in the fall of 2020. Children must turn 5 on or before September 1, 2020 to be eligible. Please learn more by visiting www.fmsd.org/apps/pages/dualimmersion.

#FMSDGlobalLearners

¡Nos encanta nuestro programa #VietnameseDualImmersion! ¡Les da a nuestros estudiantes la oportunidad de hacerse bilingües y biliterados!

Cada programa inscribirá a niños que ingresarán a kindergarten en el otoño de 2020. Los niños deben cumplir 5 años el 1 de septiembre de 2020 o antes para ser elegibles. Para obtener más información, visite www.fmsd.org/apps/pages/dualimmersion.

#FMSDGlobalLearners
